                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was reading a number of posts in this forums which advocated the use of Beserker Spirit to keep Shiny Bob alive. I've never been very happy with Shiny Bob before since he's never been able to tank without me acting as a decoy for him. I distinctly remember my level 4 animation never being able to take even a rat unless I was there to take the hits for him so the idea that he could be used to solo with struck me as a particulary iffy suggestion.
<br />

<br />
However last night  I wanted to go to Torg Mines to scout out how I might get the ore for my Scryers Trespass spell quest. I entered via the ladder at the Dulak Armoury area and found the mines empty except for a level 63 shaman. Since the zone line is very accessible in that area I decided that I might as well try a bit of soloing rather than quit and go back empty handed.
<br />

<br />
As to my front I could see a miner and a huge troll my first instinct was to charm the troll and use it to bludgeon the miner into extinction. This worked pretty well until I started to notice some very bad ping issues and this climaxed with me LDing exactly as I pulled the next mob. Heart in mouth I had to reboot my system to free the lock EQ had put my system into and to my great relief I found that somehow I had survived and had not been dumped back to my bind point.
<br />

<br />
After a further two LD's within the space of 10 mins I decided two things 1) charm solo was too dangerous with a connection this dodgy and 2) something was seriously wrong with this zone (I tested this later by camping and logging into the bazaar and a connection that was absolutely terrible in the mines was totally rock solid in a packed out bazaar - this leads me to suspect that the torg mines zone has some serious issues that need fixing)
<br />

<br />
So how to reduce the risk of dying on an LD with a dodgy connection? With a sigh out came my level 49 Shiny Bob as a desperate last ditch attempt to save the evenings play. Having read about beserker spirit I decided that I might as well try it and if everything went wrong I'd make a dash for the zone line and hope my Rune V was enough to save me.
<br />

<br />
Well as expected Shiny Bob took a licking. By the time the dark blue miner mob was down to 95% he was down to 15% this despite the fact that he was hasted and the mob was slowed. Then I chain cast Beserker Spirit on shiny bob expecting very little.
<br />

<br />
WOW....... what happened.
<br />

<br />
All of a sudden the mob stopped attacking bob and he stopped losing hp. Then he successfully tanked the mob down to 20% where I then let loose with the roots and nukes. One dead mob and one severely smug looking shiny bob.
<br />

<br />
OK so it's taken a long time to get to the question but here it is - what exactly happened to Shiny Bob when I cast Beserker Spirit on him? Why did the mob stop attacking him, was it just constantly being stunned? How does the absorb damage part of the spell affect his hp.
<br />

<br />
Essentially what the heck happened that caused Wimpy Bob to suddenly turn into Tank Bob with just that spell?
<br />

<br />
Please, I'd like a sensible explanation of this occurance because it's clear to me that I'm not understanding the implications of this spell.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
