                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One thing I found in the mines is that the miners are lower level, so charming them is probably preferable to charming the guards. <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="icon_lol.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
The MR, even after tash, is quite high on everything in Torgirans. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I ALWAYS had Shiny Bob tanking, but that meant I had to pull, So make sure that you have a damage shield up on both bob and yourself. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If you have the plat Rune is your (AND Shiny Bob's) friend.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_axe.gif" alt="icon_axe.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
It could be that bob got better attack with the fake rune, and then was able to land  couple bash's, thereby stunning the mob for you. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  My pattern on the miners was pull with slow, dot (extra debuff), then wait for Bob to taunt it off me and meanwhile refresh the fake runes (bedlam now) once I saw the fade message (or noticed dmg).  You can even med and then just be ready to nuke once they turn.  For the guards, being higher level and hitting much harder than the miners I did the complete debuff route.  Mez, cripple, weaken, slow, mem blur, then asphyxiate and hope bob could get agro quicker. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Its a lot easier to solo since bob heals so much faster than we do. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I found that given best haste (wonderous) bob can bash fairly regularly, even if it doesnt always work. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Even dual weilding be aware that Bob will bash, and once you get a high enough pet.
<br />

<br />
The fake runes do nothing for Bob's HP, but since it's essentially a componentless rune, it works the same way, and the higher strength increases Bob's attack.  If you start the fight with bob having that kind of strength buff, he hits for max a LOT more often. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Torgiran miners are unfortunately green or lt blue to me now, and even some of the guards are starting to head that direction.  But where you are fighting is fairly safe exp, you just have to be careful with Bob's tendency to push the mob.  I have lost more mobs by having them pushed through the wall by bob, and they wander around trying to get back into the mine geometry, usually for about a half hour then just poof. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />  And of course sometimes you WILL see a rather heavy train come running in. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I duo'd myself with a wizard in the mines pretty much to 60. I found it to be the most reliable experience I could get, even if it didn't go to fast.  The bloodguards and such would be better if you kite near the nadox zone line, but are much more dangerous. Good luck, the fake rune approach is something I found myself hunting in Jagedpine in my 40's and it made me and the pet really nasty.  I would berserker myself, and use fire elemental since I didn't have feedback.  Pull, dot, then work on your melee skills, once berserker fades, step back and recast on yourself, then step in and melee. In the mines you cant really do that as well, but it is possible, and Bob can do his best Ginsu interpretation. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Nysa Stargazer, Phantasmist of the 60th Veil
<br />
Follower of Erollisi Marr, Searching for Essence of Vampire</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
